{"PubmedArticle": [{"MedlineCitation": {"SpaceFlightMission": [], "OtherID": [], "InvestigatorList": [], "OtherAbstract": [], "CitationSubset": ["IM"], "KeywordList": [], "GeneralNote": [], "PMID": "17881930", "DateCompleted": {"Year": "2008", "Month": "01", "Day": "03"}, "DateRevised": {"Year": "2007", "Month": "09", "Day": "20"}, "Article": {"ArticleDate": [], "Language": ["eng"], "ELocationID": [], "Journal": {"ISSN": "0192-0790", "JournalIssue": {"Volume": "41", "Issue": "9", "PubDate": {"Year": "2007", "Month": "Oct"}}, "Title": "Journal of clinical gastroenterology", "ISOAbbreviation": "J Clin Gastroenterol"}, "ArticleTitle": "Tormentil for active ulcerative colitis: an open-label, dose-escalating study.", "Pagination": {"StartPage": "834", "EndPage": "838", "MedlinePgn": "834-8"}, "Abstract": {"AbstractText": ["Tormentil extracts (TE) have antioxidative properties and are used as a complementary therapy for chronic inflammatory bowel disease. In individual patients with ulcerative colitis (UC) positive effects have been observed.", "To assess the safety, pharmacology, and clinical effects of different doses of TE in patients with active UC.", "Sixteen patients with active UC [clinical activity index (CAI) >/=5] received TE in escalating doses of 1200, 1800, 2400 and 3000 mg/d for 3 weeks each. Each treatment phase was followed by a 4-week washout phase. The outcome parameters were side effects, CAI, C-reactive protein, and tannin levels in patient sera.", "Mild upper abdominal discomfort was experienced by 6 patients (38%), but did not require discontinuation of the medication. During therapy with 2400 mg TE per day, median CAI and C-reactive protein improved from 8 (6 to 10.75) and 8 (3 to 17.75) mg/L at baseline to 4.5 (1.75 to 6) and 3 (3 to 6) mg/L, respectively. During therapy, the CAI decreased in all patients, whereas it increased during the washout phase. Neither undegraded nor metabolized tannins could be detected by liquid-mass spectrometry (LC-MS) in patient sera.", "TE appeared safe up to 3000 mg/d. Tannins from TE are not systemically absorbed. The efficacy in patients with UC should be further evaluated."]}, "AuthorList": [{"AffiliationInfo": [{"Identifier": [], "Affiliation": "Department for Internal Medicine II, University Hospital Freiburg, Germany. roman.huber@uniklinik-freiburg.de"}], "Identifier": [], "LastName": "Huber", "ForeName": "Roman", "Initials": "R"}, {"AffiliationInfo": [], "Identifier": [], "LastName": "Ditfurth", "ForeName": "Amelie V", "Initials": "AV"}, {"AffiliationInfo": [], "Identifier": [], "LastName": "Amann", "ForeName": "Frank", "Initials": "F"}, {"AffiliationInfo": [], "Identifier": [], "LastName": "G\u00fcthlin", "ForeName": "Corina", "Initials": "C"}, {"AffiliationInfo": [], "Identifier": [], "LastName": "Rostock", "ForeName": "Matthias", "Initials": "M"}, {"AffiliationInfo": [], "Identifier": [], "LastName": "Trittler", "ForeName": "Rainer", "Initials": "R"}, {"AffiliationInfo": [], "Identifier": [], "LastName": "K\u00fcmmerer", "ForeName": "Klaus", "Initials": "K"}, {"AffiliationInfo": [], "Identifier": [], "LastName": "Merfort", "ForeName": "Irmgard", "Initials": "I"}], "PublicationTypeList": ["Clinical Trial, Phase I", "Journal Article", "Research Support, Non-U.S. Gov't"]}, "MedlineJournalInfo": {"Country": "United States", "MedlineTA": "J Clin Gastroenterol", "NlmUniqueID": "7910017", "ISSNLinking": "0192-0790"}, "ChemicalList": [{"RegistryNumber": "0", "NameOfSubstance": "Plant Extracts"}, {"RegistryNumber": "0", "NameOfSubstance": "Tannins"}, {"RegistryNumber": "9007-41-4", "NameOfSubstance": "C-Reactive Protein"}], "CommentsCorrectionsList": [{"RefSource": "J Clin Gastroenterol. 2007 Oct;41(9):797-8. doi: 10.1097/MCG.0b013e3180684255", "PMID": "17881923"}], "MeshHeadingList": [{"QualifierName": [], "DescriptorName": "Adolescent"}, {"QualifierName": [], "DescriptorName": "Adult"}, {"QualifierName": [], "DescriptorName": "Aged"}, {"QualifierName": ["drug effects", "meta